**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
	TRIALS 	
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************

*************************************************************
Phase 1
*************************************************************

Note: trial.phase1_positions
* assigns the rectangles and circles of the various colors to their respective (randomly determined) positions
for phase 1
<trial phase1_positions>
/ ontrialbegin = [
	shape.lS_red.hposition = list.largeRx.nextValue;
	shape.lS_red.vposition = list.largeRy.nextValue;
	shape.lS_green.hposition = list.largeRx.nextValue;
	shape.lS_green.vposition = list.largeRy.nextValue;	
	shape.lS_blue.hposition = list.largeRx.nextValue;
	shape.lS_blue.vposition = list.largeRy.nextValue;	
	shape.lS_yellow.hposition = list.largeRx.nextValue;
	shape.lS_yellow.vposition = list.largeRy.nextValue;
	shape.lS_purple.hposition = list.largeRx.nextValue;
	shape.lS_purple.vposition = list.largeRy.nextValue;
	shape.lC_red.hposition = list.largeCx.nextValue;
	shape.lC_red.vposition = list.largeCy.nextValue;
	shape.lC_green.hposition = list.largeCx.nextValue;
	shape.lC_green.vposition = list.largeCy.nextValue;	
	shape.lC_blue.hposition = list.largeCx.nextValue;
	shape.lC_blue.vposition = list.largeCy.nextValue;	
	shape.lC_yellow.hposition = list.largeCx.nextValue;
	shape.lC_yellow.vposition = list.largeCy.nextValue;
	shape.lC_purple.hposition = list.largeCx.nextValue;
	shape.lC_purple.vposition = list.largeCy.nextValue;	

]
/ trialduration = 0
/ recorddata = false
</trial>

Note: trial.phase1_instructions
* present the instructions for the current trial (either new or repeat)
<trial phase1_instructions>
/ ontrialbegin = [
	if (values.repeat == 0) {
		values.itemnumber = list.instructions.nextValue;
		values.attempts = 0;
		values.remainingduration = parameters.phase1_timelimit;
		values.trialcount_phase += 1;
	}
]
/ stimulusframes = [1 = phase1_instructions]
/ trialduration = parameters.instructionsduration
/ recorddata = false
/ branch = [
	return trial.phase1;
]
</trial>

Note: trial.phase1
* presents the set up for phase 1
* waits for mouse click input
* evaluates the response
* calls trial.phase1highlight
	values.touch_x = trial.phase1.responseX;
	values.touch_y = trial.phase1.responseY;

<trial phase1>
/ inputdevice = mouse
/ ontrialbegin = [
	values.points = 0;
	values.attempts += 1;
]
/ stimulusframes = [1 = background, lS_red, lS_yellow, lS_blue, lS_green, lS_purple, lC_red, lC_yellow, lC_blue, lC_green, lC_purple]
/ validresponse = (lS_red, lS_yellow, lS_blue, lS_green, lS_purple, lC_red, lC_yellow, lC_blue, lC_green, lC_purple, background)
/ iscorrectresponse = [
	return(trial.phase1.response == item.phase1_correctresponses.item(text.phase1_instructions.currentItemNumber));
]
/ ontrialend = [
	values.instructions = text.phase1_instructions.currentItem;
	values.touch_x = mouse.x;
	values.touch_y = mouse.y;
	
	if (trial.phase1.correct) {
		if (values.attempts == 1) {
			values.points = 2;
		} else {
			values.points = 1;
		}
	}
	values.totalpoints += values.points;
	values.phasepoints += values.points;
	
	if (values.attempts == 1 && trial.phase1.error){
		values.repeat = 1;
	} else {
		values.repeat = 0;
	}
]
/ branch = [
	if (trial.phase1.latency < values.remainingduration){
		return trial.phase1highlight;
	} else if (trial.phase1.response == 0 && values.attempts == 1){
		return trial.repeatproblem_phase1;
	} else {
		return trial.nextproblem;
	}
]
/ timeout = values.remainingduration
</trial>

Note: trial.phase1highlight
* presents an 'x' where the mouse was clicked
* calls trial.repeatproblem_phase1 or trial.nextproblem 
<trial phase1highlight>
/ stimulusframes = [1 = background, lS_red, lS_yellow, lS_blue, lS_green, lS_purple, lC_red, lC_yellow, lC_blue, lC_green, lC_purple, pointer]
/ trialduration = 17
/ recorddata = false
/ branch = [
	if (values.repeat == 1){
		return trial.repeatproblem_phase1;
	} else {
		return trial.nextproblem;
	}
]			
</trial>

Note: trial.repeatproblem_phase1
* alerts participant to try the same problem once more
<trial repeatproblem_phase1>
/ stimulusframes = [1 = background, feedback]
/ trialduration = parameters.iti
/ recorddata = false
/ branch = [
	return trial.phase1_instructions;
]
</trial>


